output_list.impact: The morphToken function generates a random value, which is used to set the balance of an arbitrary user. This can be used for malicious purposes, allowing attackers to gain access to other users' assets.
The payWinner function uses the balance of the owner as a tax, instead of a fee. This allows the owner to gain access to other users' assets.
The KingOfEther contract allows any user to set the owner. This can be used for malicious purposes, allowing unauthorized access to other users' assets.
The AURA contract has an integer overflow, allowing the owner to gain access to other users' assets.
